1... c5
{ If not for this timely move, White would consolidate on the kingside, go Kh1, Rg1 and be the one attacking. Now how Black gets counterplay on the light squares and get to the e5 pawn in time. }
2. e3
{ White completely panics. A normal move such as Bg4 would have kept the balance.   21.Bg4  Bc6  22.Qc4  Qxe5  23.Qxc5  fxg3  24.e4  gxh2+  25.Kh1  h5  26.Bh3  Rac8  27.exd5  Bxd5  28.Rxd5  Rxc5  29.Rxe5  Rxe5  30.Kxh2  Re2+  31.Kg3  Rd8  is one crazy line provided by the computer where the rook and pawn are worth two bishops, though no more. }
