[White "Svetushkin, Dmitry"]
[Black "Igor Vladimirovich"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rn2qrk1/p1pbb1pp/1p2pn2/2Pp1p2/PP1P4/5NP1/1B2PPBP/RN1Q1RK1 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

1... a5
{ White went too fast to the queenside with his pawns. When facing a pawn phalanx, don't panic and look if you can trade them or whether moving forward makes them stronger or weaker. }
2. cxb6
{ 12.b5  bxc5  13.dxc5  c6 !  No need to pick up the c5 pawn right away, it's not going anywhere. First Black weakens the a4-b5 complex further. }
2... axb4 3. bxc7 Na6 4. Ne5 Nxc7
