4... Rc7 5. f3 Ng5 6. Rxc7 Qxc7 7. h4 Ne6 8. Bh3 g6 9. Nc3 Qe7 10. Qd2 Nd8 11.
Ne2 Bxe2
{ Black's bishop was so useless he would have traded it for a chicken crossing the road. The remaining Black pieces are still terrible and he loses without a fight over the light squares. }
12. Qxe2 Nc6 13. Kf2
{ Now White improves his pieces one by one, starting with the king. He is completely in control and playing for two results, so it is a good moment to end the trainable line. }
13... a5 14. Nd3 Kf7 15. Qc2 Qb7 16. Bf1
{ This actually happens to be the winning concept in a few moves : the bishop had no hope to crash through f5 with levers on e4 or g4. }
16... Kg7 17. Qc3 Kf7 18. Be2 Kg7 19. Nf4 Kf7
{ A blunder but Black was still struggling to survive anyway. } 20. Ba6
{ Now the White queen penetrates and devours every single little pawn. } *


