[White "A Stonewall Concise Repertoire"]
[Black "2-e4"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 f5 2. e4 fxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 g6 5. f3 d5
{ In general going d5 after f3 is a good policy against gambits in the Dutch. }
6. Qd2 Bg7 7. O-O-O Nc6 8. h4
{ you can now take the f3 pawn, which is slightly dangerous, or just play h5 and Bf5 and smugly ask what the fuss was all about. }
